# paint.type AI Manifest (Level 4)

This is the AI manifest for the `src/paint_core/fuzz/fuzz_targets/` directory (Level 4) of paint.type.

## Purpose

This manifest describes the purpose and structure of the `src/paint_core/fuzz/fuzz_targets/` directory.

## Authority Split

- **Central protocol authority:** `standards/` repository
- **Local integration authority (this directory):** src/paint_core/fuzz/fuzz_targets/ specific configurations

## Canonical Files\n\n- `pt_tile_blit.rs` -- pt_tile_blit configuration or data\n- `pt_layer_opacity.rs` -- pt_layer_opacity configuration or data\n- `pt_tile_write_pixel.rs` -- pt_tile_write_pixel configuration or data\n\n## Invariants

1. All A2ML state files must live in `.machine_readable/` ONLY, never in the repo root.
2. Each directory at layer 4 must have its own `0.4-AI-MANIFEST.a2ml`.
3. Each directory must have a `README.adoc` describing purpose, contents, and function.
4. SPDX license identifiers must be consistent across all files (PMPL-1.0-or-later).

## Startup Checklist for Agents

1. Read this file (`0.4-AI-MANIFEST.a2ml`).
2. Read `README.adoc` for directory overview.
3. For subdirectories, navigate to their respective manifest files.
4. Never edit `.machine_readable/` files directly.
